name: Savana Datah
address: Unnamed Road 80852, Datah, Abang, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80852, Indonesia
review 1: This is look like unknown savana in Bali, not big like Savana Tianyar, however this savana very closed to the unknown beach, very peaceful beach in Kubu Tulamben, Bali. I can say if you go thru the small street to the north, you will found the beach and if you go back to the south, you can see the small savana with mounth Agung as a background. No need to pay anything to get there, it just keep it clean. So that we can help to save the earth.
review 2: I accidentally found this place while riding on the road to Kintamani via Kubu. In dry season the landscape looks more dramatic yet beautiful, it seems that I was somewhere in Flores. The view is amazing: Savannah, dry grass, dry trees, palm trees, blue ocean and mount Agung.
review 3: You may find some solitude here. This place is quite secluded and you may enjoy the view of mount Agung, breeze to windy afternoon.
review 4: Nice spot if you are creative enough to take pictures.
